Because of this I play with PC names off to reduce my video lag and packet loss. I'll outline what my version of events are, but I doubt you'll care anyways, nobody seemed to care enough to ask me what happened anyway.<br>
<br>
1. I was kiting Lodizal far from buffing area, and had no idea where I was on the island in relation to CC or Slivers.<br>
<br>
2. Caziel says that they're ready for him. So I hit track and tracked Caziel. I run with lodz in a bee-line straight to him.<br>
<br>
3. Since my PC names were off, I had no clue that the group of people there wasn't my intended target, however, Slivers had decided to buff about 20 relative feet from where CC was doing their CR.....I found this rather perplexing after the fact.<br>
<br>
4. I ran to the group, thinking it was Slivers, which partly I was correct...since Slivers was so damned close to CC. I ran through and inadvertantly caused a wipeout....<br>
<br>
If I had been kiting on the south side of the island instead of the north, would this even be an issue? Do you think I'd intentionally train your guild when my guild already had the power to kill the mob presant, and killing rights to it since I was kiting it? Something doesn't add up sir...<br>
<br>
I don't expect you to believe me, but please just remember.<br>
There are 3 sides to every story, yours, mine, and the truth.<br>
<br>
Thankyou Baldrik, and again, I'm sorry if you or your guild foster and bad feelings towards me. You're a great bunch of people and I hope that someday you realise the truth.<br>
